{"title_page": "Robert Alan Shields Jr.", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{Unreferenced|date= May 2017}}\n{{External links|date= May 2017}}\n{{Notability|date= May 2017}}\n}}\n\n'''Robert Alan Shields Jr.''' (January 23, 1975 &ndash; August 23, 2005) [http://www.1prison.com/shields.html] was a convicted [[murder]]er who was [[capital punishment|executed]] in the state of [[Texas]] for the murder of Paula Stiner on September 21, 1994.\n\nShields broke into the house of Paula and Tracy Steiner and ransacked it. When Paula Stiner returned home, Shields fatally stabbed her and robbed the house. Shields used one of the victim's credit cards and was later caught driving her car. [[DNA]] evidence was instrumental in his conviction.\n\nShields argued at his appeal that he had ineffective counsel, and that, although he was in the victim's home, he was not the actual killer. The arguments were rejected by the court. [http://www.democracyinaction.org/dia/organizations/ncadp/campaign.jsp?organization_KEY=206&campaign_KEY=1036][http://www.christiannetworks.org/pages/issuesfall05.html]\n\nShields wrote a letter to Texas Governor [[Rick Perry]] [http://www.1prison.com/shields.html] inviting [http://www.txexecutions.org/reports/348.asp] him to witness his execution.\n\nHe was executed on August 23, 2005, by [[lethal injection]].[http://www.deathpenaltyinfo.org/article.php?scid=8&did=1264]\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.oag.state.tx.us/oagnews/release.php?id=1115 Texas Attorney General statement before Shields' execution]\n* [http://www.democracyinaction.org/dia/organizations/ncadp/campaign.jsp?organization_KEY=206&campaign_KEY=1036  National Coalition to Abolish the Death Penalty]\n* [http://www.tdcj.state.tx.us/statistics/deathrow/drowlist/shields.jpg Offender Information]. ''[[Texas Department of Criminal Justice]]''. Retrieved on 2007-11-15.\n* [http://www.tdcj.state.tx.us/stat/shieldsrobertlast.htm Last Statement]. ''[[Texas Department of Criminal Justice]]''. Retrieved on 2007-11-15.\n* [http://www.clarkprosecutor.org/html/death/US/shields980.htm Robert Alan Shields Jr.]. ''The Clark County Prosecuting Attorney''. Retrieved on 2007-11-15.\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Shields, Robert Alan Jr.}}\n[[Category:1975 births]]\n[[Category:2005 deaths]]\n[[Category:21st-century executions of American people]]\n[[Category:21st-century executions by Texas]]\n[[Category:American people convicted of murder]]\n[[Category:People executed by Texas by lethal injection]]\n[[Category:People executed for murder]]\n[[Category:People convicted of murder by Texas]]\n\n{{Crime-stub}}\n{{US-crime-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{Unreferenced|date= May 2017}}\n{{External links|date= May 2017}}\n{{Notability|date= May 2017}}\n}}\n\n'''Robert Alan Shields Jr.''' (January 23, 1975 &ndash; August 23, 2005) [http://www.1prison.com/shields.html] was a convicted [[murder]]er who was [[capital punishment|executed]] in the state of [[Texas]] for the murder of Paula Stiner on September 21, 1994.\n\nShields broke into the house of Paula and Tracy Steiner and ransacked it. When Paula Stiner returned home, Shields fatally stabbed her and robbed the house. Shields used one of the victim's credit cards and was later caught driving her car. [[DNA]] evidence was instrumental in his conviction.\n\nShields argued at his appeal that he had ineffective counsel, and that, although he was in the victim\u2019s home, he was not the actual killer. The arguments were rejected by the court. [http://www.democracyinaction.org/dia/organizations/ncadp/campaign.jsp?organization_KEY=206&campaign_KEY=1036][http://www.christiannetworks.org/pages/issuesfall05.html]\n\nShields wrote a letter to Texas Governor [[Rick Perry]] [http://www.1prison.com/shields.html] inviting [http://www.txexecutions.org/reports/348.asp] him to witness his execution.\n\nHe was executed on August 23, 2005, by [[lethal injection]].[http://www.deathpenaltyinfo.org/article.php?scid=8&did=1264]\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.oag.state.tx.us/oagnews/release.php?id=1115 Texas Attorney General statement before Shields' execution]\n* [http://www.democracyinaction.org/dia/organizations/ncadp/campaign.jsp?organization_KEY=206&campaign_KEY=1036  National Coalition to Abolish the Death Penalty]\n* [http://www.tdcj.state.tx.us/statistics/deathrow/drowlist/shields.jpg Offender Information]. ''[[Texas Department of Criminal Justice]]''. Retrieved on 2007-11-15.\n* [http://www.tdcj.state.tx.us/stat/shieldsrobertlast.htm Last Statement]. ''[[Texas Department of Criminal Justice]]''. Retrieved on 2007-11-15.\n* [http://www.clarkprosecutor.org/html/death/US/shields980.htm Robert Alan Shields Jr.]. ''The Clark County Prosecuting Attorney''. Retrieved on 2007-11-15.\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Shields, Robert Alan Jr.}}\n[[Category:1975 births]]\n[[Category:2005 deaths]]\n[[Category:21st-century executions of American people]]\n[[Category:21st-century executions by Texas]]\n[[Category:American people convicted of murder]]\n[[Category:People executed by Texas by lethal injection]]\n[[Category:People executed for murder]]\n[[Category:People convicted of murder by Texas]]\n\n{{Crime-stub}}\n{{US-crime-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: \u2019s \u2192 's", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_Alan_Shields_Jr."}
{"title_page": "Chakai (Vidhan Sabha constituency)", "text_new": "{{Short description|Assembly constituency in Bihar, India}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date = March 2020}}\n\n{{Use Indian English|date = March 2020}}\n\n{{Infobox Vidhan Sabha constituency|name=243 Chakai|district=[[Jamui district]]|state=[[Bihar]]|lok_sabha_constituency=[[Jamui (Lok Sabha constituency)]]|mla=Savitri Devi|parl_name=[[Bihar Legislative Assembly]]}}\n'''Chakai (Vidhan Sabha constituency)''' is an assembly constituency for [[Bihar Legislative Assembly]] in [[Jamui district]] of [[Bihar]], [[India]]. It comes under [[Jamui (Lok Sabha constituency)]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://jamui.nic.in/constituencies/|title=Constituencies {{!}} Welcome to Jamui District Official Website {{!}} India|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elections.in/bihar/assembly-constituencies/chakai.html|title=Chakai Election and Results 2018, Candidate list, Winner, Runner-up, Current MLA and Previous MLAs|website=www.elections.in|access-date=2020-03-05}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Assembly constituencies of Bihar]]\n\n\n{{Bihar-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|Assembly constituency in Bihar, India}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date = March 2020}}\n\n{{Use Indian English|date = March 2020}}\n\n{{Infobox Vidhan Sabha constituency|name=243 Chakai|district=[[Jamui district]]|state=[[Bihar]]|lok_sabha_constituency=[[Jamui (Lok Sabha constituency)]]|mla=Savitri Devi|parl_name=[[Bihar Legislative Assembly]]}}\n'''Chakai (Vidhan Sabha constituency)''' is an assembly constituency for [[Bihar Legislative Assembly]] in [[Jamui district]] of [[Bihar]], [[India]]. It comes under [[Jamui (Lok Sabha constituency)]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://jamui.nic.in/constituencies/|title=Constituencies {{!}} Welcome to Jamui District Official Website {{!}} India|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elections.in/bihar/assembly-constituencies/chakai.html|title=Chakai Election and Results 2018, Candidate list, Winner, Runner-up, Current MLA and Previous MLAs|website=www.elections.in|access-date=2020-03-05}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Assembly constituencies of Bihar]]\n", "name_user": "GargAvinash", "label": "safe", "comment": "+{{Bihar-geo-stub}} usingStubSorter", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chakai_(Vidhan_Sabha_constituency)"}
{"title_page": "Winnetka, Illinois", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->| name = Winnetka, Illinois\n| native_name = \n| native_name_lang = <!-- ISO 639-2 code e.g. \"fr\" for French. If more than one, use {{lang}} instead -->\n| settlement_type = [[Suburb]]\n| image_flag = \n| flag_alt = \n| image_seal = \n| seal_alt = \n| image_shield = \n| shield_alt = \n| nickname = \n| motto = \n| image_map = File:Cook County Illinois Incorporated and Unincorporated areas Winnetka Highlighted.svg\n| mapsize = 260px\n| map_caption = Location of Winnetka in Cook County, Illinois\n| image_map1 = Illinois in United States (US48).svg\n| map_caption1 = Location of Illinois in the United States\n| coordinates = {{coord|42|6|22|N|87|44|16|W|display=inline,title}}\n| coor_pinpoint = \n| coordinates_footnotes = \n| subdivision_type = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n| subdivision_name = {{US}}\n| subdivision_type1 = [[U.S. state|State]]\n| subdivision_type2 = [[County (United States)|County]]\n| subdivision_type3 = [[Civil township|Township]]\n| subdivision_name1 = [[Illinois]]\n| subdivision_name2 = [[Cook County, Illinois|Cook]]\n| subdivision_name3 = [[New Trier Township, Cook County, Illinois|New Trier]]\n| established_title = [[Municipal corporation|Incorporated]]\n| established_date = 1869\n| founder = \n| seat_type = \n| seat = \n| government_footnotes = \n| government_type = [[Council\u2013manager government|Council-manager]]\n| leader_party = \n| leader_title = [[President (government title)#Sub-national|President]]\n| leader_name = Christopher Rintz\n| leader_title1 = \n| leader_name1 = \n| unit_pref = Imperial\n| area_footnotes = <ref name=\"CenPopGazetteer2016\">{{cite web|title=2016 U.S. Gazetteer Files|url=https://www2.census.gov/geo/docs/maps-data/data/gazetteer/2016_Gazetteer/2016_gaz_place_17.txt|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=Jun 30, 2017}}</ref>\n| area_magnitude = <!-