{"title_page": "Ratlam Junction railway station", "text_new": "{{one source|date=January 2019}}\n{{third-party|date=January 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2016}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=September 2015}}\n{{More citations needed|date=March 2011}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name            = Ratlam Junction\n| native_name     = \u0930\u0924\u0932\u093e\u092e \u091c\u0902\u0915\u094d\u0936\u0928\n| type            = [[Indian Railways|Indian Railway]] [[Junction Station]]\n| style           = Indian railway\n| image           = Ratlam Junction (2).jpg\n| image_size      =\n| image_caption   =\n| address         = Station Road, Ratlam, Madhya Pradesh\n| country         = India\n| coordinates     = {{Coord|23.340758|75.050992|type:railwaystation_region:IN|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n| elevation       = {{convert|493.620|m|ft}}\n| line            = [[New Delhi\u2013Mumbai main line]]\n| other           =\n| structure       =\n| platform        = 7\n| tracks          =\n| code            = {{Indian railway code\n  | code = RTM\n  | zone = [[Western Railways]]\n  | division = [[Ratlam railway division]]\n  }}\n| owned           = [[Indian Railways]]\n| status          = Functioning\n| map_locator     = {{Location map|India Madhya Pradesh|lat=23.340758|long=75.050992|width=300|caption= Location in Madhya Pradesh|label= '''Ratlam Junction''' railway station}}\n}}\n'''Ratlam Junction railway station''' is a major rail junction on the [[New Delhi\u2013Mumbai main line]] of [[Indian Railways]].\n\n==Administration==\n[[File:Ratlam Junction.jpg|thumb|Ratlam Junction]]\nIt comes under [[Western Railways]] zone of [[Indian Railways]]. [[Ratlam]] is one of the busy and [[revenue]] generating junctions for Western Railways.{{cn|date=January 2019}}\n\n== Services ==\nRatlam junction is a major junction & Divisional Headquarter of Western Railway & Madhya Pradesh Ratlam is well connected from New Delhi, Mumbai, Pune, Banglore, Mysore,Chennai, Nagpur, Bilaspur, Jammu, Howara and Chittorgarh junction, Ajmer, Gaya etc.\n2 Rajdhani express & all Duranto express commercial stoppage at Ratlam Junction.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://indiarailinfo.com/arrivals/ratlam-junction-rtm/304  Trains at Ratlam]\n\n{{Top 100 booking stations of Indian Railways}}\n{{Railway stations in Madhya Pradesh}}\n\n[[Category:Railway junction stations in Madhya Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Ratlam railway division]]\n[[Category:Railway stations in Ratlam district]]\n\n{{MadhyaPradesh-railstation-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{one source|date=January 2019}}\n{{third-party|date=January 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2016}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=September 2015}}\n{{More citations needed|date=March 2011}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name            = Ratlam Junction\n| type            = [[Indian Railways|Indian Railway]] [[Junction Station]]\n| style           = Indian railway\n| image           = Ratlam Junction (2).jpg\n| image_size      =\n| image_caption   =\n| address         = Station Road, Ratlam, Madhya Pradesh\n| country         = India\n| coordinates     = {{Coord|23.340758|75.050992|type:railwaystation_region:IN|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n| elevation       = {{convert|493.620|m|ft}}\n| line            = [[New Delhi\u2013Mumbai main line]]\n| other           =\n| structure       =\n| platform        = 7\n| tracks          =\n| code            = {{Indian railway code\n  | code = RTM\n  | zone = [[Western Railways]]\n  | division = [[Ratlam railway division]]\n  }}\n| owned           = [[Indian Railways]]\n| status          = Functioning\n| map_locator     = {{Location map|India Madhya Pradesh|lat=23.340758|long=75.050992|width=300|caption= Location in Madhya Pradesh|label= '''Ratlam Junction''' railway station}}\n}}\n'''Ratlam Junction railway station''' is a major rail junction on the [[New Delhi\u2013Mumbai main line]] of [[Indian Railways]].\n\n==Administration==\n[[File:Ratlam Junction.jpg|thumb|Ratlam Junction]]\nIt comes under [[Western Railways]] zone of [[Indian Railways]]. [[Ratlam]] is one of the busy and [[revenue]] generating junctions for Western Railways.{{cn|date=January 2019}}\n\n== Services ==\nRatlam junction is a major junction & Divisional Headquarter of Western Railway & Madhya Pradesh Ratlam is well connected from New Delhi, Mumbai, Pune, Banglore, Mysore,Chennai, Nagpur, Bilaspur, Jammu, Howara and Chittorgarh junction, Ajmer, Gaya etc.\n2 Rajdhani express & all Duranto express commercial stoppage at Ratlam Junction.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://indiarailinfo.com/arrivals/ratlam-junction-rtm/304  Trains at Ratlam]\n\n{{Top 100 booking stations of Indian Railways}}\n{{Railway stations in Madhya Pradesh}}\n\n[[Category:Railway junction stations in Madhya Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Ratlam railway division]]\n[[Category:Railway stations in Ratlam district]]\n\n{{MadhyaPradesh-railstation-stub}}\n", "name_user": "2405:205:c86a:dab3::2ad8:78b0", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ratlam_Junction_railway_station"}
{"title_page": "Rollin 60's Neighborhood Crips", "text_new": "{{onesource|date=August 2018}}\n{{Infobox Criminal organization\n| name                = Rollin 60's Neighborhood Crips\n| image               =\n| caption             =\n| founded             = 1976\n| founding location   = [[Los Angeles, California]]\n| years active        = 1976 \u2013 present\n| territory           = \n| ethnicity           = Black\n| membership est      = 6,000 to 8,000<ref name=\"LaDaily\"/>\n| criminal activities = bank robberies, drug trafficking, homicide, assault,carjacking and vandalism<ref name=\"LaDaily\"/>\n| allies              = [[Rollin 40's]] and [[Rollin 90's]] NHCs<ref name=\"LaDaily\"/>\n| rivals              = [[Bloods]],  \"Hoover factions\"<ref name=\"LaDaily\"/>\n}}\nThe '''Rollin 60's Neighborhood Crips'''  is a street [[gang]] based in [[Los Angeles, California]], originally formed in Los Angeles in 1976 from the Westside [[Crips]] and have since spread to other cities in the United States.<ref name=\"LaDaily\"/> Membership is estimated to be between 6,000 and 8,000 people, making it one of the largest gangs in the Los Angeles area.<ref name=\"Covey2015\">{{cite book|last=Covey|first=Herbert C. |title=Crips and Bloods: A Guide to an American Subculture: A Guide to an American Subculture|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=F5RzCQAAQBAJ&pg=PA159|date=2015|publisher=ABC-CLIO|isbn=978-0-313-39930-5|page=159}}</ref>\n\nMembers identify themselves by wearing [[Seattle Mariners]]<ref name=\"Covey2015\"/> or [[Chicago White Sox]] logos and mark areas they are in with graffiti.<ref name=\"LaDaily\"/>\n\nAccording to the ''[[Los Angeles Daily News]]'' in 2004, Rollin' 60's was \"the largest black criminal street gang in the City of Los Angeles with over 1,600 active members \u2013 the size of an Army brigade. \"<ref name=\"LaDaily\">{{cite news|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20041012065238/http://lang.dailynews.com/socal/gangs/articles/dnp5_culture.asp|archive-date=October 12, 2004|url=http://lang.dailynews.com/socal/gangs/articles/dnp5_culture.asp|title=Rollin 60s give unique window into gang culture|first=Beth|last=Barrett|work=Los Angeles Daily News|date=September 30, 2004}}{{dead link|date=March 2018}}</ref>\n\nTwo men identified as members of the Rollin' 60 were arrested for the 1984 murders of four members of professional football player [[Kermit Alexander]]'s family. Police say the gang members got the address wrong and killed the wrong family.<ref>{{cite most rolling 60s crips bang the 6 point star because folk and crip where once Allies news|url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9E07E6DE1039F936A35752C1A962948260|title=Two Gang Members Arrested In Alexander Family Killings|work=The New York Times|date=November 5, 1984}}</ref>\n\nMusician, businessman, and community activist [[Nipsey Hussle]] was a member of the Rollin 60's Neighborhood Crips.<ref name=\"NYT 2019-04-19\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/19/us/nipsey-hussle-death-california-gangs.html|title=Nipsey Hussle Was Hailed as a Hero. But to California Officials, He Was Still a Gangster.|last=Arango|first=Tim|date=2019-04-19|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-04-20|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Crips}}\n\n[[Category: Crips sets]]\n[[Category: African-American gangs]]\n\n\n{{crime-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{onesource|date=August 2018}}\n{{Infobox Criminal organization\n| name                = Rollin 60's Neighborhood Crips\n| image               =\n| caption             =\n| founded             = 1976\n| founding location   = [[Los Angeles, California]]\n| years active        = 1976 \u2013 present\n| territory           = \n| ethnicity           = Black\n| membership est      = 6,000 to 8,000<ref name=\"LaDaily\"/>\n| criminal activities = bank robberies, drug trafficking, homicide, assault,carjacking and vandalism<ref name=\"LaDaily\"/>\n| allies              = [[Rollin 40's]] and [[Rollin 90's]] NHCs<ref name=\"LaDaily\"/>\n| rivals              = [[Bloods]],  \"Hoover factions\"<ref name=\"LaDaily\"/>\n}}\nThe '''Rollin 60's Neighborhood Crips'''  is a street [[gang]] based in [[Los Angeles, California]], originally formed in Los Angeles in 1976 from the Westside [[Crips]] and have since spread to other cities in the United States.<ref name=\"LaDaily\"/> Membership is estimated to be between 6,000 to 8,000 people, making it one of the largest gangs in the Los Angeles area.<ref name=\"Covey2015\">{{cite book|last=Covey|first=Herbert C. |title=Crips and Bloods: A Guide to an American Subculture: A Guide to an American Subculture|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=F5RzCQAAQBAJ&pg=PA159|date=2015|publisher=ABC-CLIO|isbn=978-0-313-39930-5|page=159}}</ref>\n\nMembers identify themselves by wearing [[Seattle Mariners]]<ref name=\"Covey2015\"/> or [[Chicago White Sox]] logos and mark areas they are in with graffiti.<ref name=\"LaDaily\"/>\n\nAccording to the ''[[Los Angeles Daily News]]'' in 2004, Rollin' 60's was \"the largest black criminal street gang in the City of Los Angeles with over 1,600 active members \u2013 the size of an Army brigade. \"<ref name=\"LaDaily\">{{cite news|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20041012065238/http://lang.dailynews.com/socal/gangs/articles/dnp5_culture.asp|archive-date=October 12, 2004|url=http://lang.dailynews.com/socal/gangs/articles/dnp5_culture.asp|title=Rollin 60s give unique window into gang culture|first=Beth|last=Barrett|work=Los Angeles Daily News|date=September 30, 2004}}{{dead link|date=March 2018}}</ref>\n\nTwo men identified as members of the Rollin' 60 were arrested for the 1984 murders of four members of professional football player [[Kermit Alexander]]'s family. Police say the gang members got the address wrong and killed the wrong family.<ref>{{cite most rolling 60s crips bang the 6 point star because folk and crip where once Allies news|url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9E07E6DE1039F936A35752C1A962948260|title=Two Gang Members Arrested In Alexander Family Killings|work=The New York Times|date=November 5, 1984}}</ref>\n\nMusician, businessman, and community activist [[Nipsey Hussle]] was a member of the Rollin 60's Neighborhood Crips.<ref name=\"NYT 2019-04-19\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/19/us/nipsey-hussle-death-california-gangs.html|title=Nipsey Hussle Was Hailed as a Hero. But to California Officials, He Was Still a Gangster.|last=Arango|first=Tim|date=2019-04-19|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-04-20|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Crips}}\n\n[[Category: Crips sets]]\n[[Category: African-American gangs]]\n\n\n{{crime-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: between 6,000 to \u2192 between 6,000 and", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rollin_60%27s_Neighborhood_Crips"}
